Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Pop the chunks onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Spicy Mayo ==

Meanwhile, halve the @chilli{1} lengthways, deseed, then thinly slice.

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{2}.

Cut the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

In a #small bowl{}, mix the @mayo{2%sachets} with the @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet}, then set aside.

== Glaze ==

To make your glaze, in a separate small bowl, mix together the @ketjap manis{1%sachet}, @red Thai style paste{1%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @oil{1%tbsp}.

> Double both for 4p.

== Sesame Broccoli ==

Place a pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the broccoli, @sesame seeds{1%sachet} and chilli (use less if you don't like spice) and fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Lower the heat and allow to cook until the broccoli is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

== Steak ==

Wipe the pan and return to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Season the @21 day aged Irish sirloin steak{250%g} with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Once the pan is hot, fry the sirloin until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for medium-rare.

Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it more well-done.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

== To Finish ==

When the steaks are almost ready, pour the glaze into the pan, cook for ~{1%minute}, then remove from the heat.

Turn the steaks in the glaze to evenly coat them, then transfer to a #plate{}.

Cover with foil and allow to rest for ~{1-2%minutes}.

When rested, thinly slice the steaks and transfer to your #plates{}.

Spoon over any remaining glaze from the pan.

Serve the sesame broccoli and potatoes alongside.

Add a dollop of chilli mayo for dipping and sprinkle over the scallion to finish.